76561198002911957,Recommended,266840,28735882,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,LORD OF THE HARVEST,"The hours played on Steam pale greatly with the amount of hours I have put into this game. Still owning it in a hard copy...This is one of those games I always come back to.Not because the story is any good, it's the equivalent of a Hercules or Xena episode.Not because the gameplay is revolutionary.Not because of cutting edge graphics...So why?It's fun.It allows us to interact with myths and mythology in a way that's surprisingly rare.It is an RTS with a solid base building mechanic.The factions are unique from one another with those factions being further seperated by a multitude of minor god selections which help diversify and specialize your force.The game mostly works (in a generally) on a rock/paper/scissors mechanic...with mythological units (like a Minotaur or a Sphinx) eat up basic normal units, your hero units (say an egyptian pharaoh or Hercules) beat myth units and your basic normal human units beat hero units.The game does have its faults. Obviously the graphics aren't the best. The story is below average, the base building mechanics are from another time but you get to have Hercules knocking around giants while on another part of the map a sphinx unit spins to win on a structure.As with most games I'll recommend, snag it on sale but ultimately I suggest you give it a chance."
