,Recommended,266840,28922724,Posted: 1 January,all,Raregreek,"I have spent an overwhelming time playing Age of Mythology back in the disk form years ago. I was overly hyped to see that Steam was picking up AOM considering I lost the disk some time ago. Let's go over the game, shall we?(This will be solely based off of Age of Mythology itself, rather than any updates or such done by the Extended Edition.)Campaign32 levels, 3 different factions, interesting heroes and a compelling story. Barely any levels are the same, with each being unique and exciting. While a few (and I mean a very few) are a tad bland, that should be no reason to turn someone away from it. Not to mention the Atlantis campaign, which adds 12 more levels to play on with another new story and heroes tying to the first campaign in many ways.SkirmishWhen playing skirmish, the game provides a fun and (admittedly slightly repetative) experience to better oneself before possibly attempting multiplayer or the campaign on a harder difficulty. The player can choose any of the factions and their respective gods, giving a nice plethora of play styles. I do recommend keeping away from the ""Titan"" difficulty, however, as the AI gains a lot of handicaps.MultiplayerOh boy, multiplayer. I've seen a lot of great things from it. New maps, game mods, (usually) differing play styles from other players. It offers a good zone for both new players and pros, but I do recommend avoiding many ranked matches unless you're at the top of your game, because trust me, the other player almost always is. It's a great way to spice things up if you've beaten the campaign and are tired of the AI in skirmishes.Extended Edition + China DLCThe extended edition and China DLC are honestly... Disappointing. I'd say avoid the China DLC unless you're dying for new content so badly you'd do anything for it (which I'd even recommend the workshop before the DLC). The Chinese army is very gimmicky, and everything feels reused, with little, if anything, being brand new. It's also rather buggy. I, myself, haven't even beat the campaign yet, it's just bland and boring. The Extended edition tried to amp up textures and such, but it makes some things ugly and unappealing, and I highly recommend getting a mod or two to fix these up.All in all, I say buy this game, be it the disc or the Steam version, avoid the China DLC and game on. You won't be disappointed!"
