,Recommended,266840,25452081,"Posted: 10 September, 2016",all,The Techno Union Army,"As you can see I've quite a bit of playtime on this game so clearly I do enjoy playing it. However the review system on steam is ""Do you recommend this game?"" And there I say no. But do I recommend it to previous Age Of Mythology and Titans expansion players? Yes.This game is great fun especially if you play a lot of scenario maps, classics like escape are always good fun or tower defence. I barely ever play the base game my self I always play user generated game modes and while they are VERY good they are subject to the same bugs and crashes and flaws as the rest of the game. The desync bug seems very rare now for several months I havent had it but maybe thats just my luck. That said random crash to desktops can happen upon starting a match online. Some people report issues with running the game, even when they have a good hardware setup. It has been fine for me. I actually play in 1440p maxed capping my self at 60fps it seems to never drop without good reason.Most of the time I play without these crashes but when it does happen it is extremely frustrating as you can wait some times half an hour to fill a lobby with people. (online is not dead but its a small and close community.)So the run down is fans of the original, especially scenario players, will be happy with being able to play all of the new scenarios which are being developed by the same people who did all those years ago on AOM Heaven.Fans who played the original and mostly played supremacy and the occasional scenario like world map are still catered for but will not see much difference apart from the new OP chinese gods (they are the new atlantis). Though desyncs dont really happen now you may still get random crashes on launching a match.Those who never played before well it's a good rts even its base game supremacy mode which im still just as bad at is pretty fun and there are a lot of new players who play supremacy so you wont be alone. But you learn how buggy the game can be. Not so much in gameplay but stability. You may be better off with the original game using some third party software for online. Though if you do that the people you will play are going to be experienced players.Either way I think if you're going to buy this wait until there is a sale. It drops all the time during every major sale to quite a low price. And during those times instead of seeing 20-50 people in the general lobby during peak times you will see over 100 because of all the noobs. So its a good time to start and will save you some money.Don't buy this at full price."
