,Recommended,266840,10072171,"Posted: 10 May, 2014",all,Velma Dinkley,dance
,Recommended,266840,19443233,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,<LDS> AngelHunter,"This is an honest review on Age of Mythology: Extended Edition.First off, a couple sentences about me so you know who this review is comming from.I started this game when I was 3 and my dad was playing it and he got me into it (it was escpecially fun because I am Greek and this helped me out in Mythology so when I went to 3rd grade in the Mythology class I literally knew everything even if some things arent 100% accurate to real mythology). I started the original version that came out in, I believe, 2001. Fast-forward a couple of years and I got theTitansversion of the game bringing a whole newfaction (I will get into factions later). I lost the game when my old 9 year old laptop broke and I got it back some time ago when it went on a steam sale for 7 Euros. If the non-steam versions of the game tracked my hours aswell, I would easily have more than 1500.The main idea of the gameThe game is anRTS(Real time strategy), you get to command your villagers to gather resources, make your town, your army and even your navy and fight to the death with your enemies!You can choose in between 5 factions (Greek, Egyptian, Norse, Atlantean and Chinese)Every faction has 3 different ""Main gods"" (ex. Greeks have Zeus, Poseidon and Hades)Every faction and main god has a few different upsides and downsides. (ex. Hades has very good archers)There are 4 types of resources used to upgrade units,buildings and much more,Wood, Food, Gold and Favor(Favor is used to create mythical units like Minotaurs or get some God-Specific upgrades)You can also advance to different ages if you have the right resources( Archaic -> Classic -> etc (I typed this because I dont remember the names lol)When advancing to a new age you can select some ""sub-gods"" like Aphrodite or Hermes which all give different upgrades and myth units (ex. Athena gives Minotaurs) and ofcourse a god-power that is 1-use on most factions (ex. Ares gives the ""pest"" power which is used on enemy ""unit-producing"" buildings will make them unable to produce units for a short time.Those were the gameplay basicsThe current state of the game/communityThe game was created in 2001 as I said before. It was pretty succesful and a very fun RTS game.A few years later the ""Titans"" update came out (I believe this was around 2006).The titans update added some cool new features and a whole new faction, the Atlanteans!And after that. The game basically died. The developers company disbanded and the game and community was left in avery bad spot. Then at 2014 ""Extended edition"" came out on steam. It had its upsides and downsides. The majority of the community sticked to titans. That remained this way until 2015 where a new update came out. It added the Chinese faction and a whole new campaign with like 15 levels.The campaign was overall bad and all the myth units/gods felt really rushed and overpowered. The new designs for some myth units were litteraly other myth units recolored with a dragon head which spitted fire that could destroy any building in like 2 seconds. Very overpowered and not fun.That was for the ""updates"" part of the game. Now we will talk about the community which is basically dead. If you are on the game you will see that there are only like 25 people online at all times so its nearly impossible to get an online game unless you like to wait for like 3 hours or can convince some of your friends to get this game.The ratingsGraphics:6.5 (For a very old game the graphics arent bad, but the bad graphics also have an upside of some sort since even lower end PC's can run it.)Campaign:8/10 (The campaign is amazing to say the least. Personally for me it gave me nostalgia after playing it again after 8 years but if you are an RTS player you will definetly like the campaign)Community:6/10 (The community at its current state isnt very good. The easiest way and probably the only way to play online currently is with friends,(The offline isnt very bad either tho, the bots especially on higher difficulties can  show a big challenge))Gamemodes:8/10 (I would have combined gamemodes with the community but AoM is the type of game that you can literally make anything out of, a few examples: Roleplay, Settlers, a map of litterally THE WHOLE WORLD YOU CAN PLAY ON and much more)OVERALL RATING FOR AOM:EE :7.5/10ConclusionIf you are an old player who played the titans version and possibly even the original you should give this game a try but maybe when its on a sale when its usually on 7 Euros.For new players seeing this game for the first time: If you are interested on this game you can read some more reviews or watch some youtube videos of it to get you to try it out, or if you have friends who are also interested in this game, get it on a sale if you have the money to spare and enjoy the game with your friends for guaranteed hours of fun! Good luck!"
