76561198364745636,Recommended,266840,30384475,Posted: 7 March,all,Silly Goose,"Age of Mythology has a tremendous amount of depth to it, and it would be  a shame for it to be down-rated due to poor graphics or other such novelties. The original developers really put a lot of thought into the economy, dynamics of civilizations, war play tactics, and ensuring that its consumers have the ability to run away with their imaginations in their map making sandbox.Many people tend to look over the small details that makes this game great, which is unfortunate.This game offers not only a  variety of extremely dynamic civilizations with varying god powers, strengths, and both passive/active procs such as priest that convert wild animals, buildings that when razed spawn militia, sky passages, andetc.But, it also provides great depth in the everyday game play.For example, ranged units generally have percent based accuricies that generally drop when against a moving target (which allows for great micro management in battles and a depth of skill and dynamic to warfare), cetain units have differents strengths and weaknesses, myth units come with a great varity of abilities that range from healing, to freezing, to acids spit, and the ability to eat trees or gold mines to heal oneself.There is also dynamic source of resources that vary with which the speed one can gather them and the amount they come in.And as I mentioned before, u have access to a map making sandboxes, and many players have created all types of scenerios such asSettlersZeldaNeo mutationBlood CastleRole Playing  MapsEscapeZonesand much more for different playing styles/modes.Now I have only touched the Iceburg, but I hope u get the chance to see the potential in the game, and the communities within it."
