,Recommended,266840,11952089,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,Rattlesnake8,"This game was incredible when it first came out. The remake has done a great job in updating the game and bringing it back for old fans and new comers alike. If you were a fan of any of the ""age of"" games, or like RTS, or just looking for something to try, pick this game up.The different sides all play differently, god powers add a new layer of strategy and the mythical setting is different to what you normally see and interesting.The campaign has a great story, the skirmish and multiplayer are a lot of fun and this is a game that will keep you busy for a long time to come. 10/10"
76561198019336779,Recommended,266840,10087258,"Posted: 11 May, 2014",all,h4n4,"I have owned the original AoM since it's release and it is one of my favourite games. I never had the Titans expansion so that's why I bought this remake/Extended Edition/whatyouwannacallit. Visuals are great and music is still memorable. Campaign keeps you well occupied but the objectives are just repetitive sometimes. You usually start with a few villagers and your task is to destroy enemys camp. Repeat that and repeat it again. Still I keep coming back because the story is very good for a strategy game, as you could expect from AoE series. Maps in classic skirmish and campaign modes are also often very detailed and so it encourages you to scout every black spot to find hidden relics which can help you with your mission.The myth units bring a nice new twist to the old RTS formula but matches dont become a Minotaur spamfest as myth units are usually much more expensive than regular human units. Famous folklore heroes like Hercules and Achilles are also there and they take mythic beasts down like the bosses they are. Everything is pretty nice and balanced like a rock-paper-scissors game.Gods from old greek, egyptian and nordic mythologies play a major part in game. Every civilization has 3 main gods and they all have six minor gods who give you different kind of god powers like meteorite rain, ability to mind control monkeys or making your villages to gather food faster (lame!). A well used god power can turn a game upside down but they can be used only once so when and where to use them is critical.If you already own AoM and it's expansions don't bother buying this as theres very little new to offer for oldtimers. But if you don't have AoM what are you waiting for? This game is accessible for newcomers and offers a fair challenge for hardened strategy veterans. Buy it and love it!"
,Recommended,266840,10057860,"Posted: 8 May, 2014",all,Caps,I have been playing this game since 2005 and it was nice to finally play this game again with new textures. Of course there are also a few things that were added. Steam Workshop is one of them and it makes downloading mods much easier. Twitch was also built into the game to make live streaming the game easier. Day and night was also added to give a realistic feel to the game when playing on a map for a long time.The graphics on the game are good along with a few other things but I found a few things to be a bit too polished. Overall I found Age of Mythology EX to be a great game if you are into RTS games and enjoy a good story line.
