76561197981682000,Recommended,266840,12193877,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,Hovis1974,"A fantasic RTS with a Mythology Theme. Set along the same lines as the Age of Empire series, The story driven gameplay will keep you up late for just ""one more mission"". I first played this one many years ago and still continue to play it today.If you played the AOE series or any other RTS on the market, then you know that formula is the same. You build up a town for resource collection, eventually building up defenses and finally an army to destroy the opposition, rinse and repeat. But wait, That's not all. Some missions give you an army and a goal in the very beginning where you must use only that army to overcome your obstacles. You also work with three different Mythologies. Greek, Egyptian, and Norse Mythologies are represented well. Once you reach the requirements to reach the next ""age"" you can choose between two specific gods and their powers to enhance your army or buildings.A very lengthy campaign will keep you busy for hours and the varied gameplay will keep you interested....recommended? Absolutely"
