,Not Recommended,266840,33101633,Posted: 1 July,all,goldenchocolate,"I'm writing this review as someone who used to love playing AoM:TT when I was younger, it was essentially my favorite game. Therefore, it was only natural for me to want to get AoM:EE. However, if you don't have that nostalgia factor going for you, I'm not entirely sure that it's necessarily worth getting. It's not a bad game, and the campaigns alone will keep you busy for a while. Furthermore, the storyline, and thematic aspects of the game are pretty great. But despite these positive points, it's simply a very old RTS at this point, and as a result, its actual gameplay is simply not as good as what other games can offer nowadays.If, on the other hand, you also have the nostalgia factor going for you, then I would still hesitate before getting this. The DLC and patches only ruin the experience. Honestly, being unable to play the Chinese without paying (way too much for what you're getting) and then being matched up online against someone playing the Chinese is downright ridiculous.tl;drI loved AoM when I was younger. But I honestly don't think it's worth it at full price, considering what you're getting. I don't regret buying it, but I also wouldn't recommend it for most people."
