76561197972222660,Not Recommended,266840,33596291,Posted: 16 July,all,matb,"Amazingly, the new owners of this game have managed to make it far worse than the formerly excellent Age of Mythology. The units have the worst pathfinding across maps that I've seen in 30 years of gaming, frequently getting caught on hillsides, in trees, or against walls. I seem to spend 20% of my time unhooking trade carts from blades of grass that are apparently insurmountable objects in this version. I'm truly stunned that the game was released in this state.Another utterly infuriating change that has made the game considerably worse - once teams have surrendered, their units, including Titans, will continue not only to attack you, but to chase you all over the map! If you're out, you should cease to have ANY role in the game. The game should delete all units and offensive buildings to free up RAM and processor resources and should get lost! I don't expect defeated players to continue obstructing me!Add to that, occasional crashes as the game becomes too busy, and multiplayer file sizes that I still find incredible, and you could think that this game is not worth buying and at full price you'd be absolutely right. I bought it in the sale for under £10 and I guess it's not so bad for that price.Positives? New races, new missions, great new map types, decent network and online support with a surprisingly large and active community, and the fact that the game exists at all in 2017, let alone on steam with new graphics.This is my favourite of the Age series, and it's as enjoyable as I remember, with epic 2-4 hour games passing in the blink of an eye! It's much more frustrating thanks to all the new flaws. Nevertheless, this is in some ways an advance over the Microsoft version, albeit a horrifically flawed and bugged version.Love the game, hate the lazy programming. No way I can give this an honest thumbs up. I'm sure nostalgia has earned many of its good reviews, whilst others were written before people discovered its many major shortfalls."
