,Recommended,266840,18421714,"Posted: 10 October, 2015",all,UmbreonMessiah,"It's twelve years later and this game is still a blast to play. It's gotten so much publicity that it's even got a new expansion coming out after over a decade of silence.From the same minds that produced Age of Empires, Age of Mythology puts you in charge of ancient warriors and pantheons in a struggle to conquer the map. Gather food, wood, gold and Favor from your Gods in order to expand, conquer and acquire. New to the format are Myth Units and God Powers: use your accumulated favor to obtain unique improvements and powerful creatures from legends. Call upon your Gods to create food from nothing, plagues of locusts or rain fire from the skies on your enemies.In the game's 13 years of existence, it has seen 2 expansions: The Titans, and more recently Tale of the Dragon. The Extended Edition comes with The Titans expansion, which grants access to the Atlantean Civilization, an offshoot of the Greeks who have been abandoned by the traditional Gods and choose to worship the precursors to the Olympians, the Titans. As well, the Extended Edition has new online support, allowing you to play games with people from across the world and upload to Twitch immediately."
,Recommended,266840,18546202,"Posted: 18 October, 2015",all,Gary Glitter,"As a kid I LOVED AoM, so buying this for me wasn't a hard choice, but here are the positive and negatives of the game.Positives:-The game still plays like it did, so re-learing the controls is not an issue.-Fall of the Trident+ New Atlantis+ Golden Gift campaigns completely unchanged. The story has a verygood plot, with indepth detail and historical references (Helen of Troy.)- Steam Workshop added (I know hardcore fans prefererd AoM heaven over Steam Workshop, however I much prefer the ease of Steam Workshop)-Multiplayer battles with friends-Wide Screen HD (Finally)-It is on steam (No more remembering that 16 digit code on the instruction booklet you were fairly sure you threw away.)Negatives:- Online battles agaisnt strangers, and rankings (This is one of the most BROKEN online multiplayer I have ever seen. The online games will disconnect whenever they feel. The rankings can just loose data every now and then for no apparent reason.)- Over a year of no bug patches (Fix the online system!)-The Price. This is a big one, now I bought this on sale for £6.99, which is an acceptable price, but at full price for £23?! It is too much (Note you can buy an Old Disk copy of AoM for about £2-£6 online.) I would be happy to pay that much if there was a constant dev team adding and fixing content, but for a simple bog standard re-release, it is too much.-Loading times. I remember the Titans Expansion pack had long loading times, but some of the campaign loading times are ridiculous.Overall I would reccomend this game for anybody who wants to feel the nostalgia of the game, but ONLY when it goes on sale. The game at full price is not worth the money, but at sale I could say it is well worth it. The campaigns story is very good in itself, but if you finish the story line you can always turn to mods."
