76561198275797441,Recommended,266840,20869129,"Posted: 31 January, 2016",all,Pajehu63,"Not bad, bu had to say i expected a little more.The repackage on this is priceless. ""EXTENDED EDITION"" isn't really tuned up to anything special. It seems like they literally just put in the maps for the next expansion (The all too common, ""upgrade to play this!"") as a carrot on a stick for Dragon.  Oh, and NIGHT AND DAY GUYS. haha.You still have some pretty herp a derp AI and building kinks that are true to the original.  My units still love going around my city, when i have perfectly good gates X DIf this is a game you miss having on your shelf,  you enjoy the mechanics of the Age of Empires games, and or have a hard on for good mythology... Buy it if it's on sale. have to say it's worth the 7 dollars i payed.If you havent played these games yet and this one caught your eye, keep a few things in mind. The campaign really isn't anything spectacular, and it lacks the depth that many other RTS have that are available for a competitive price. There's no real negotiating trades or territories or treaties. Diplomacy is clicking to go to war.Nation-building is insanely straightforward. Laborers gather each supply, and theres very few to keep track of. Food, gold, wood, favor, population. You dont have to keep them happy or worry about maintaining them (save from your enemies wrathful armies)Combat isn't anything flashy, little units slash at eachother. There are a few little tactical things you can make them do but nothing compared to some of the other RTS games you might have played.Tl;drFun and simple RTS for all skill groups, great mythology and skirmish play. Campaign lacks luster and the ""Extended Edition"" just feels like Titans with added teasers for the Dragon Expansion. Worth a couple bucks if it's on sale(I got mine for seven dollars and that seems like a fair price).BoogaBooga."
