76561198034337114,Not Recommended,266840,10466102,"Posted: 13 June, 2014",all,Magnus the Great,"I wounld't recommend this game, at least at it's current state. Now, I am one of the fortunate people that didn't encounter any problems launching or playing the game. There are multiple issues I have with this game.The first issue isn't really game breaking, its just notable FPS drops in multiplayer. While internet connections between players no doubt is an important factor in this, but like many others who are experiencing it (Development team admitted this is an issue with coding in the patch notes), its not only the internet connections that is casuing the issue, like I said, its not game breaking.The second problem certianly is game breaking for me, it's the poor or almost non-existent ""Attack Move"" button in this game. I have played many other RTS games, I have never seen such a badly implemented ""Attack Move"" function in an RTS game. It happened to me and my friend multiple times, if you use the ""Attack Move"" function, the units would often ignore all the enemy/hostile units in the way, the units would not attack untill they reach the location or being stopped in the pathway. That is not how an ""Attack Move"" function should work. I believe this is also to do with the poor pathfinding in this game. Units would often get stuck between various objects in the map (Trees, mines, buildings, etc.).The third problem, while this is a minor one, but it is still noticable and affect the gaming experience. There are certain areas on the maps that you cannot build buildings on, again,  it's another bug, it gets rather frustrating when you are trying to build a wall, but the game won't allow you.To have more of an idea the number of issues this game current has, please check out AoM:EE Issues for the Competitive Community by DragonQ. It has highlighted many other issues I didn't address in this review. I don't think this game deserves the 30 dollar price tag at its current state. I welcome these ""HD Editions"" or ""Extended Editions"" of classic RTS games, only if it is done properly."
