,Recommended,266840,14565440,"Posted: 20 February, 2015",all,Reaper of Foreskin,"I'm probably biased because this was my first RTS ever, but this is probably the best of the genre. All the goodness of Age of Empires combined with the depth of mythological units and god powers. Don't pay attention to my hours, I had a physical copy since I was in 4th grade.Pros:+Fun challenges, it allows you to tackle the enemy at your own pace so long as you play smart and hold off against their attacks.+The Vanilla campaign + Expansion campaign can clock in about 30 hours+4 ""cultures"", basically 4 civilizations, each with 3 different major gods. Major can impact everything from your units, your god powers and your economy. For example, the Norse have 3 major gods: Loki, Thor and Odin. Loki focuses more on military, Thor focuses more on economy and technology, and Odin is a balance of both. All three of these civilizations have access to most of the same units and buildings though.+Multi-player+Titans are the tightest♥♥♥♥♥♥everCons-$30 for a 2002 game.-Has workshop support but the modding community is long gone.-Atlantis civs are OP.  Not a huge gripe because there's no competitive scene but it's important to know.If you like RTS, buy it, you'll get your moneys worth no problem."
