76561198082895965,Recommended,266840,28607790,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,RhastaSenpai,"Disclaimer: Bought the game along with the DLC, and no launch problems whatsoever, not even on multiplayer, the only problems I had was with the game itself having bugs, but never game crashing bugs.Been an Age of Mythology fan for years on, when I saw this game on steam, with ""enhanced graphics"" and all, I was really excited to buy it, and relive the memories I had when I was a little kid, playing this amazing game, it is a shame that the original developer studios Ensemble, have disbanded a long time ago, with that in mind, we can see that this version is made by another studio, on top of the work of the previous developers, the graphics are neat (with some exceptions in models and textures), as well as some minor improvements over the gameplay, but I can see now, as playing the dlc as well, that this was rushed, or if not rushed, this was a lazy attempt to make a remastered edition, the campaign from ""Tale of the Dragon"" doesn't have the magic the original campaigns had, the chinese units are cool, and the lore is okay, but the campaign has bugs, as well as poor writing also the plot at times looses its meaning, (and somehow the main campaigns have presented bugs that oiriginally weren't in the original game). Looking at the perspective of the dlc single player campaign: Doesn't live up to the legacy the original Game and The Titans expansion; even the Golden Gift campaign left. Not by one bit, if you want to buy it, wait for a sale, I did that, and for less than 9$ this is worth it, the multiplayer community is not very active, but there is people to play with.The multiplayer experience is quite different, and I gotta say playing as the Chinese, is really fun, the new maps, and remastered maps look amazing, and gladly the multiplayer doesn't have bugs that sometimes get to gamebreaking levels, the civilizations are well balanced, and as an rts this game stands great at with, with opportunities for different playstyles and strategic decisions that make a match challenging and fun. This remastered edition is okay at best, as some added features thanks to steam, it has something charming that could be amazing if it was implemented in the right way. With nothing more to say, for nostalgic ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s that probably learned more about mythology with this game than all those years in school like myself, you should probably get this.Long live the ""Age of"" games!"
