,Recommended,266840,14962530,"Posted: 19 March, 2015",all,Griffon Tempest,"Age of Mythology has always been one of - no, definitely my favourite game of all time. The campaign, though dull at times with storytelling, always had a great feel to it. Yes, sometimes, there were some things left unexplained, but it was still a good campaign. But where the game stood out was the Random Map gamemode - the game would generate a random map seed every time you played, so every time it was a little different. You could have massive free for all games involving 12 people fighting for their survival, or have a good old fashion 2v2 team battle (My personal preference).Unfortunately, I lost the disc for the Titans Expansion a while back, and have been unable to play with Titans... until now!Age of Mythology: Extended Edition is a great remake of the original AoM, with only very few differences:- Updated Graphics- A new campaign- A new multiplayer service (The original AoM lost multiplayer in 2012 I believe)- A few new random map selections (I think, they may have been in the Titans version though).- A new ""Treaty"" gamemode, and new AI types.But, what they didn't change was the gameplay, which was definitely the best part of the original game. And that means a lot to someone who loved AoM, because now, I can play on steam with my friends in the same way I would play alone against the computers.I'd say this game only has a few flaws:- Campaign can be dull at times- I often experience a lag spike for the first 5 seconds or so after starting a game.- A note on that, my CPU is 2.7 GHz dual core, and my GPU is the AMD Radeon HD 7520G (Not a very good graphics card)- Often in team games of random map, the enemy computers will gang up and want to destroy you right off the bat (Not that this wouldn't happen in a real game, but it seems it happens in Random Map games more often than not).- And, of course, its pricetag. At $30, it's a bit pricey, but still worth it in my opinion.Honestly, if this game ever goes on sale for any discount greater than 10%, get it, it's amazing for any RTS or Mythology lover."
