76561198133635604,Recommended,266840,18648045,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,Suhlippery,"TL;DRAn awesome 3 resource RTS game in which you build an army and advance through the ages with different gods and minor gods and also awesome god powers to crush your opponent and achieve victory in a mythological war. 9.5/10!pros:+replayability is unrivaled, different every time+single player story line is quite the adventure+revamped graphics and day and night cycle+god powers are cool as hell+12 different gods to play as+massive amount of different games to play onlinecons:-A.I. is kinda lackluster in the late game/on a split river map-only about 30 people online at anytime-graphics are a little dated even after revamp on steam-micro is a little pointless unless controlling a bigger unit--online servers may pop a message saying desync and immediately stop online game and goto mainmenuExcellent game its very unfortunate that more people dont play the online as there are only about 30 people online at anytime. However dont let that discourage you, the people who are online are generally willing to play a game or two with you. There is also a massive abundance of different game modes and custom maps that other players have created and brought to the online.The single player story line is rather linear, but it is yet an epic quest that is waiting for you to take on. The single player features many of the playable gods and is rather challenging when playing on the harder difficulties.The replayability is unrivaled as there are 12 different gods to play as and each having 6 minor gods to worship as you advance through the ages. Each minor gods also has its own specific units and upgrades to go along with it. Even on a random map its still fun to play alone with different combination of teammates and enemies to face off against.The graphics are a little outdated but it is an older game being 13 years old. However the lovely people who brought this game to steam have revamped some of the graphics and added a day and night cycle to which you can have on or off depending on your preference.There is one HUGE downside to the online play however. Im not sure what causes it but the servers tend to be a little unstable. Meaning while playing a game online a message will pop up saying server has become unsynched, and will immediately end the game you're in and bring you to the main menu. Unfortunetly you will also have to close out of the game completely and reboot the game on steam to be able to get back into the online menu otherwise it wont let you back in.But other than that id say this game is amazing, and dont let my hrs played fool you ive owned this game since a few months after it came out and id say i have well over 2,000hrs into this game. Every day id come home from school and play this game until i went to bed.Extremely Addicting and fun as all hell! 9.5/10!"
