76561198023197820,Recommended,266840,19960551,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,Captain Optimist,"I recommend this on the basis that it's Age of Mythology including the expansion.In my opinion the enhancements are bare (the ""improved"" water made it hard to spot fish schools at points). If you can get the original game + expansion for less than steam wants then you're probably not missing much.Good things include: both the original campaign and The Titans expansion campaign both having a slew of different objectives instead of ""build a base, go here and kill these"" of course you usually need some slight variation of that since this is an RTS after all. Factions sometimes with wildly different playstyles, for example the norse workers can only build farms, all other buildings require infantry troops. God powers which can allow you to do anything from summoning a rock which huntable animals flock around to having an earthquake ravage an enemy base (or yours if you're not careful).Bad things include: I'm not sure how balanced the game is, the atlantean faction being the big one: most their god powers can be used multiple times and their (quite expensive) workers don't need to drop off the resources gatherered anywhere. The difficulty settings need some work, on easy the ai will just sit there and wait to be destroyed, most harass you will encounter can be a ship or two assaulting your harbor now and then, while on moderate the ai will sent small squads almost to no end to harass and there's nothing in between those."
