,Recommended,266840,17452941,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,THE KRAKEN,"This is another one that I’ve spent many an hour playing; both recently and in days gone by.Age of Mythology: Extended Edition is the high definition remake of the classic Age of Mythology RTS game series from SkyBox Labs and Ensemble Studios.The GoodIf your a fan of the Age of Empires franchise, you’re most likely going to be a fan of Age of Mythology. It’s AoE with a legendary twist and some cool new features to go along with it. By far, my favorite thing about this game is the Vikings. Well…and the Kraken, but I’m biased there.God Powers were, I feel, a really cool addition to the game. Is your opponent stealing your resources and/or just being an asshat? Boom! Lightning Bolt! That’s right sucker. But, really, the God Powers are awesome and, depending on which pantheon you choose for your civilization you get different powers. Not all of them are offense oriented, however. There are some that can attract more animals to your town so that you can get more food.Myth Units were another great addition. Sending a horde of Einherjar or Anubites after your opponent is always a good time and a half.The BadAs with Age of Empires II: HD Edition, my complaint for AoM:EE is the non-updated unit graphics. It’s been a long time since this masterpiece was unleashed upon us mere mortals and very little seems to have been done to dress it up.The MehThe price tag is rather steep for as old a game as this.Verdict: YeaAge of Mythology: Extended Edition is a must have for fans of the AoE franchise and lovers of mythology alike. It’s a great, solid RTS to add to your collection. The next time you see it pop up on sale, I’d jump on it. As always, thanks for reading."
