76561198046539253,Recommended,266840,17990112,"Posted: 11 September, 2015",all,"$erpent453, Swaggot of Swagnia","This is the best game I have ever played. Not even joking. Never, in the entire history of my life, have I played a game I enjoyed more than this one. Everything about it is wonderful, or at least in my opinion they are.First off, the amount of mythology that's in the game is, for the most part, a dream come true for me. I've always been a fan of the mythology from Greek and Norse times, so a game based around that sort of thing is pure awesome.The gameplay itself is stellar for an RTS game. More or less standard stuff, you build a base, build an army, kill everyone. However, it is so smooth and so rewarding seeing your accomplishments once you've done this. It also does some other things to help seperate it from other RTS's, including using a God Power system where you can benefit yourself through various powers.The graphics are pretty darn good for a game from 2001 or earlier. The models themselves are dated, but everything else is perfectly fine by my standards.The game also has a damn good story, and an expansion pack inside it as well. Plenty of content.It also has multiplayer, which appears to have been fixed, seeing as I don't get much lag from playing it.10/10, play the ♥♥♥♥ing game already."
