 the game+ Skepan, Jegweg, Prostagma- Player base is not that big- All old maps/mods cannot be used with this version- If you play with many people/bots for quite a while, graphical bugs can appear. These can take forms of missing texture, missing minimap and stuck effects.If you are into RTS games and liked the Age of Empires series, or even played the old Age of Mythology, I 100% suggest you have a look into this. It is worth the cost, and if not, there always are steamsales, just grab it at -75% off.10/10 would stick with this game for the rest of the live."
,Recommended,266840,17525470,"Posted: 13 August, 2015",all,nbc5218,"The neglected cousin of the ""Age of Empires"" series, this mythology-themed real-time strategy is an underrated classic. It's incredibly satisfying to smite your opponent with Zeus' lightning bolt, or rain meteors down upon their city, or summon a mighty Titan to smash through their battle lines. Worshiping different gods provides different god powers, allowing for plenty of variety in play style. The single-player campaign is solid, and there's plenty of variety in maps and game modes to play stand-alone matches. This game needed a sequel. It's great."
