76561198015186142,Recommended,266840,23037833,"Posted: 17 May, 2016",all,Sandbucket,"I'm a big fan of age of mythology as evident by the amount of hours I've put into it. The campaign is quite enjoyable and many players are sufficiently satisfied with the single player experience to not have the majority of the issues bother them(most issues are regarding civ balancing and online play).The game has 4(or 5 if you get the DLC) civilizations with 3 major gods per civilization that each have their own minor god paths. These builds influence a variety of things including gathering, armies, myth units and mighty godpowers that can level buildings or temporarily summon an undead army(there's many more!).Generally the game has an accepted view on the gods and which ones are more powerful than others but for the average player everything goes and you'll never really have to worry about the limitations of your gods. Unfortunately the latest DLC that included the chinese gods did a poor job of balancing the civilization and the consensus is that they are much too powerful as things stand which may lead to people requesting not to play them.Another unfortunate part of the game is networking. Age of Mythology is a peer-to-peer game instead of hosted by a server. This means that games are prone to lag if players live far apart which may very well be the case since there is no filter for regions.Word has it there are still patches in the works to fix the networking to be more stable and to balance out the chinese civilization but the game is undeniably riddled with various bugs and balancing issues that have not seen any attention for many years. This won't bother the beginners or noob players so if you intend to play the game casually you shouldn't be too worried about the nuances of balancing civilizations and the likes.The verdict:It's a great game really. It's a lot more slow paced than games like Starcraft and the units are unique. There's plenty of players to play 1v1's, 2v2's and 3v3's but anything beyond that is very prone to lag. There's custom maps for the people who like that and a campain to give you that old-school vibe strategy games used to give. The veteran players will inevitably bash this game because their demands have grown over time but if you love strategy games the cost can very well be justified."
