76561197971176406,Recommended,266840,10663194,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,drbond408,"An absolute gem that is a must play for any Age of Empires fan (or RTS fan in general). The Extended Edition has added quite a bit of features to an already unforgettable computer game from the Windows XP era. Outside of support for newer operating systems such as Windows 8.1, the team behind the new revamped line of classic PC games for Steam audiences added stuff like TwitchTV, steam friend invites in the multiplayer lobby, new graphical effects (mostly with lighting and the new water textures), new native resolutions for widescreen monitors, and other visual tweaks mostly...but have the left the fun gameplay largely intact (for those not wanting a tainted AOM). All the great single player campaign and multiplayer content from the original AOM is here, as well as the included content from the Titans expansion pack. Probably a bit too pricey at its suggested retail price ($29.99) for a title that has recieved numerous reprints via jewel case release, but a MUST BUY if you catch this particular version on a Steam sale (especially for someone running a new monitor/GPU/OS)."
