,Recommended,266840,19901334,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,only4theweak,"A spin-off of the slightly better-known Age of Empires franchise, Age of Mythology takes the basic historical RTS formula and applies it to a wonderfully immersive fantasy world based on the myths and legends of three ancient cultures: the Greeks, Egyptians and Norse (the Extended Edition includes The Titans, an expansion pack that introduces an entirely fictional ""Atlantean"" faction to the game). The game's writers do a brilliant job of making these seemingly disparate elements fit together and work, with a surprisingly engaging story campaign, entertaining characters, iconic heroes and monsters, and a huge amount of detail that demonstrates a real passion for the source material. The game serves up fun, humour and personality in spades, and features unique ""god power"" mechanics that set it apart from similar titles and introduce a whole new level of strategy (and wanton destruction) to an already solid gameplay structure, which is both satisfyingly complex and easily accessible to new players. Whilst the Extended Edition does very little to change or improve upon the original game (not that such alterations are necessary) it nonetheless makes this cult classic available on modern systems, provides an updated community platform and features new, higher-resolution graphics and textures that make this already beautiful game even better to look at. In summary, Age of Mythology is a unique, effortlessly enjoyable strategy game, and the Extended Edition is well worth your time and money."
