76561198061442437,Recommended,266840,12172709,"Posted: 21 September, 2014",all,davidb2951,"I admit I'm walking into this with extreme bias, that is due to the fact that I actually grew up with the rts genre before moving on to other types of gaming and only recently picking it up again.Also I before even purchasing this version already thought fondly of the game series, buying the extended edition twice due to losing one copy of it, and I was extremely young, therefore you could say I grew up on it.Review Start:This enhanced edition is pretty much a slightly prettier version of the vanilla game, that being said, the vanilla game is extremely strong. Just from one of the two vanilla stories, it's worth it's price tag, and there are 2 whole stories to it, a level editor, multiplayer.There are problems with this version that weren't there in the previous versions.For one, they took out the cheat codes, even in the vanilla story mode. I personally have fond memories of giant canadian caped flying bears who would shoot laser beams to take out the strongest of enemies, of running over building with giant 4 wheelers, and so forth, which actually takes away from the enjoyment heavily.That being said, this game is still strong without the wackiness, it's a good way to get you interested in Greek Mythology like it did to me as a kid, and it's a solid rts game with decent balance and variances between the different religions/civilizations.In reality, I would rank it as one of the better rts games to my knowledge, which is extremely dated and probably took place from 14 or so years ago up to around 7 years ago. I consider this game only second to the Battle for Middle Earth series and it's deeply ingrained into my childhood.The characters are never really all that fleshed out even though you're supposed to have an attachment to the characters, especially the villains who seem like named canon fodder hero enemies, but the troops are all fairly unique to each other, even though you'll almost never be using human troops even fully upgraded in later ages (progression system in specific matches)Overall it's a solid game that's worth trying out, but the enhanced edition doesn't actually enhance anything but the water and day and night cycle when it would have been interesting to have myth troops. If you're a completionist, you'll enjoy the achievements, if you want a solid rts with an interesting theme and fun dynamics to different cultures, this is a good buy. If you're a psychopath like me, you'll also enjoy level editor where you'll talk like you're the characters and make your own story.7/10Masterpiece when viewed with nostalgia."
