,Recommended,266840,10738913,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Bobbylogic,"This is an exact copy of the original game. Lucky for me, I loved it. The visuals are very similar, with just a touch of high definition enhancement. The multiplayer is back, but not quite as popular as I had hoped. I can find a multiplayer match at nearly any time of day or night, just can't be too picky. The horrible Out of Sync error is still here, unfortunately. There are still minor bugs being fixed, but nothing too game breaking.I know a lot of that is negative but this really is a fantastic game, and it brings back a lot of good memories from when I was younger. If you like Age of Empires: 2/3 then you will have a rough draft of how the game works. I personally feel it is a little bit more complicated but much more enjoyable. It is much faster paced, even with civilizations like the Egyptions who like to boom.I would recommend this game to anyone who loves, is falling in love, or brand new to RTS games. I've been clocking in plenty of time since I bought it."
