,Recommended,266840,10353050,"Posted: 5 June, 2014",all,Razor Shell!,"First off, I would totally recommend the game. The game is worth the full price of 30 dollars, but if you are a bit tight on cash or a bit of a Eugene Krabs you could wait for a sale to pop out and reap that. I am a new player to the Age Series but when I booted up the game, I instantly loved it. One thing I absolutely love about the game is that unlike Civilization or other titles it is all real time, no waiting on your opponents/friends to make their moves, just you and your villagers. Another thing I like about this game is that it is a low-spec requiring game; no hassle over if you or your friends can run it. Multiplayer is incredibly fun with friends but alas the game is not perfect. The game is not pleasing to the eyes but you can download some texture packs to slightly remedy the problem, but really if the game is fun you shouldn't worry about how the game looks. The animation (including movement) in the game aren't so good either, at first it seemed that my game was laggy but really it was just the animations. The networking sometimes is a drag as well, when a multiplayer game is lost due to loss of connection it is difficult to get that map back and running. The campaign is good as well as the map editor. Oh, and mods. Mods are nice. tl;dr Get the game.TL;DRGet the gamePros:-Low spec game-Fun multiplayer-Real time (No waiting like Civilization games)-Steam Workshop integration-Map EditorCons:-Outdated graphics-Strange animations-Networking sometimes can be a drag-Vectoring is not that great."
