,Recommended,266840,34767727,Posted: 5 September,all,GarrickWinter,"This is a classic, and for good reason. It's a nice old RTS with a relaxed pace and a lot of character, and even though the visuals have aged considerably, there's still something special about romping across the ancient world with mythical creatures and heroes.The campaigns are a bit simplistic, but they're still fun and varied enough to be worth playing through. Each faction is quite unique in its mechanics and units, in a way that makes for a greater variety of play (though I do wish they had picked a more interesting 4th faction than Atlanteans). The core RTS mechanics are solid and enjoyable, just like what you might know from games like Age of Empires.The Steam remaster seems to be well put-together, too - I haven't had any technical or graphical issues, which is a big relief.I haven't played the new China expansion yet (and I've heard not-great things), but the core game as presented here is as fun as I remember from when I was a teen, and harkens back to better days when RTS games were plentiful and varied and not trying to be eSports."
